Risk Assessment: 

[cols=",",]
|=======================================================================
|DESCRIPTION |Y shaped wave tank that allows two children to make waves
that then combine in or out of phase.

|RISKS |Spillage of water from over-zealous children or leaks causing
slip hazard.

|ACTION TO BE TAKEN TO MINIMISE RISKS |Instruct children not to make
waves that are near to overflowing the tank. Before demonstrating check
for leaks. Have tissue paper on hand to mop up any small spillages,
keeping an eye out for water on work surface and floor.

|ACTION TO BE TAKEN IN THE EVENT OF AN ACCIDENT |In case of injury call
first aider.
